<br><br>Dolen 40 Paladin in Training <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualanen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alanen</A> at: 3/19/02 7:41:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 7:53:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Check for level 40 Please</span><hr size=1> I solo'ed BR at 42. <br><br>Some equipment help:<br><br>Gaunts of Black &gt; Deepwater gaunts. Cheaper too.<br><br>6 ac 65 HP rings, or at least 5/55's, instead of Jagged bands.<br><br>Piercing: 30/40 or better is always &gt; 20/30. Get haste and you'll kick butt... and sell that Centi Warspear for some cash.<br><br>1h/shield: I don't use 1h, and have no reccommendations as for the weapon, but for the shield I reccommend Clay Guardian (25 AC 50 HP, should run 500pp or less.)<br><br>2hs: This is junk, lol. Get yourself an ACG before you make any weapon purchases, kick butt with it, and don't ask for another sword pre-50 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>For most visible slots, start looking for Deepwater, great AC and you will eventually be able to proc it. Look for helm first, then in no particular order: bracer, boots, arms, another bracer. While 2 bracers won't have any additional effect when chain stunning over 1 bracer, the AC is good.<br><br>Legs: Crusty for the stamina. 6 STR 16 STA &gt; 1 ac and 6 STA. You will love the HP.<br><br>Face: what are you wearing in this slot? If it's one of those STR/WIS veils... TRASH IT NOW hehe. Get somthing with AC, even banded is better.<br><br>BP: Certainly  better than the bronze I had at 40 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Get an enameled black chestplate (or if you're not broke yet, treeweave) for only 500pp. Treeweave should  be 1-2k.<br><br>While you are still trying to get Deepwater, I would reccommend crusty (except keep Ro helm and arms, you'll love having good WIS. I regret not having enough WIS.)<br><br>Ears: If you're a WIS freak, get forest loops; otherwise, keep the orc fangs. I'm looking into Forest Loops over my orc fang/cougar claw combo, myself, although you aren't of a level yet when you would need to worry so much. The dex on forest loops is also good for procs.<br><br>Get haste in some slot. Beware of the FRSS and lesser guard of haste-they are only 6% haste.. not worth losing the stats in those slots. Try for a Swiftclaw Sash (15% haste with 2 AC  and 2 DEX), a Hangmans Noose (nodrop, 15% haste with 5 AC, put it in waist slot not head), or best, an FBSS (22% haste, no stats but better than the other belts I've mentioned).<br><br>Range slot: Try for a Goranga Idol. Or anything else with AC. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaleani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saleani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 7:54:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Check for level 40 Please</span><hr size=1> A faster 1hs would be good, like a Centi LS, not that I am willing to part with enough plat to buy one. Your AC is about like mine (folks tell me to get better AC, and hopefully this thread does not get hijacked into one where folks tell me to get rid of my rings and get better AC)<br><br>A place I soloed at 40 (boring as heck) and from time to time up to 45 was the entrance of Droga. Some nice quests from chardok require the deaths of thousands of goblins (2k + about 6 more per sarnak you every killed). If you can organize your own groups in Droga, the experience will be amazing (12% zone bonus to start).<br><br>On my vanity web page, I have some details about Droga, since I spent a lot of time there. I will be putting more details on the Chardok quests there as I have time to update the pages.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/saleani">www.geocities.com/saleani</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><br><br>PS. Please ignore any advice about &quot;strength of grodan&quot; since they *appear* to have stopped dropping. <p><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64195'>Combat Profile</a><br><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64207'>Tradeskill Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualanen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alanen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 8:20:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Check for level 40 Please</span><hr size=1> For face, I'm  using the cougar face mask that you can quest for in Ice Clad.   Only using centi war spear to get my piercing up Lol.  After I get it to a lvl where I can actually do some damage with piercing, I'll switch to the Light Velium War Lance 30 39.<br><br>Thanks for your help, I'll start looking for DW stuff and Gaunts of the Black.<br><br>Dolen 40 Paladin in Training <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 8:51:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Check for level 40 Please</span><hr size=1> Saleani... your rings still stink. :P<br><br>Alanen... you have very similar gear to mine, actually.  Your AC is a tad lower, but not by alot.<br><br>Here's what I've got: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=25182">Keyne Falconer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>I normally use my 2h-Practice Sword (I end up soloing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> alot</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and that DS is very nice) and then switch out to my Centi Warspear.  The Sword/Shield combo is strictly for Bash/Interrupts.<br><br>Upgrades for you...<br>Head: DW Helm.<br>Hands: Gaunts of the Black.<br>Haste: Greater Guard of Haste is sweet... wish I had one.  Otherwise go with the FBSS/Swiftclaw<br>If you get Belt-Haste, get Crested Spaulders for your Shoulders.<br><br>I personally solo the Graveyard in Katta.  You can control the pace incredibly easily, and if you're in trouble just root/fear and zone since the undead will despawn very quickly when not aggroed.<br><br>You don't mention your Race... but at this time I'm going to do my usual recomendation of Cultural Smithed Armour... see here: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_smithing_armor_stats.htm">Armour</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for stats. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualanen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alanen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 10:54:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Check for level 40 Please</span><hr size=1> I'm actually a Half Elf Paladin &lt;Dang I look good in plate : )&gt;<br><br>Diety is Mith Marr.<br><br>My stats are:<br><br>STR = Around 120<br>STA = 91<br>AGL = 100<br>DEX = 99<br>WIS = 89<br>INT = 75<br>CHA = 85<br><br>Resists:<br><br>MR=30<br>FR=40<br>CR=67<br>PR=32<br>DR=43 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualanen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alanen</A> at: 3/19/02 7:35:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 12:39:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Check for level 40 Please</span><hr size=1> Looks like you're in the same boat I was... though not quite as bad. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Get your Sta above 100.  Crusty Boots (like I wear), Crusty Greaves (I don't like the graphic though) or Crusty Vambraces (ditto).<br><br>Also, what deity do you follow?  If you're a Rodcet Nife Paladin, Imbued Field Plate gives 2 Sta &amp; 4 Wis on each piece...  Get the Boots, Mask possibly Cloak... though and Enchanted Silver cloak would be better AC (just much tougher to get).  If you're a Tunare Paladin, the Imbued Mithril (High Elf made) Cloak: AC 14, DEX 6, CHA 6, WIS 8, wt 3.0 is hard to beat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=240.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=6><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=240.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=240.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=240.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=240.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"